+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kc3Z8sNCtW9VZzU1TDjqXL","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of the entire codebase exploration:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE CODEBASE EXPLORATION REPORT\n\n### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── types.ts          (Interface definitions)\n│   │   ├── engine.ts         (BuildEngine implementation)\n│   │   ├── templates.ts      (Template factories)\n│   │   └── index.ts          (Exports)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep          (Empty - plugins to be implemented)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts          (Core tests)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       ├── dev-server.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       └── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── .git/\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. PLUGIN INTERFACE DEFINITION (src/core/types.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts)\n\n**Class: BuildEngine**\n\n**Methods:**\n\n1. **constructor(config: SiteConfig)** - Initializes with site configuration\n   - Stores private `plugins: Plugin[]`\n   - Stores private `templates: Map<string, Template>`\n\n2. **registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void** - Adds a plugin to the registry\n\n3. **registerTemplate(template: Template): void** - Registers a template by name\n\n4. **resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]** - Uses topological sort to resolve plugin execution order\n   - Detects circular dependencies → throws \"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"\n   - Detects missing dependencies → throws \"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"\n   - Returns plugins in correct dependency order\n\n5. **async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>**\n   \n   **Build Pipeline:**\n   1. Creates BuildContext with config, files copy, empty output/assets/data Maps\n   2. Gets ordered plugins via `resolvePluginOrder()`\n   3. **Phase 1 - beforeBuild hooks:** Run all beforeBuild hooks in order\n   4. **Phase 2 - transformContent hooks:** \n      - For each plugin in order:\n      - Transform all files through transformContent hook\n      - Update ctx.files with transformed files\n   5. **Phase 3 - Template rendering:**\n      - For each file, get template (default: 'default')\n      - If template exists, render with template.render(content, data)\n      - Data includes: title, slug, date, tags, metadata, siteTitle, baseUrl\n      - Store rendered output as `{slug}.html`\n      - If no template, store raw content as `{slug}.html`\n   6. **Phase 4 - afterBuild hooks:** Run all afterBuild hooks in order\n   7. Return BuildContext\n\n6. **getPlugins(): Plugin[]** - Returns copy of plugins array\n\n7. **getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>** - Returns copy of templates map\n\n---\n\n### 4. CORE TESTS (tests/core.test.ts)\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n\n| Test | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| registers plugins | Plugin registration |\n| registers templates | Template registration |\n| builds with default template | HTML rendering with default template |\n| builds with list template | HTML rendering with list template |\n| outputs raw content when no matching template | Fallback to raw content |\n| calls plugin beforeBuild hook | Hook execution |\n| calls plugin transformContent hook | Content transformation |\n| calls plugin afterBuild hook | Hook execution |\n| executes plugins in dependency order | Topological sort verification |\n| throws on circular dependency | Error handling |\n| throws on missing dependency | Error handling |\n| applies multiple plugins transformContent in order | Plugin chain |\n| provides shared data store in build context | ctx.data Map |\n| retains file metadata through build | Metadata persistence |\n| produces empty output for empty file list | Edge case |\n\n---\n\n### 5. PLUGIN TEST FILES - DETAILED SPECIFICATIONS\n\n#### **A. search-index.test.ts**\n\nCreates search index JSON in afterBuild hook.\n\n**Requirements:**\n- Plugin name: likely \"search-index\"\n- Has `afterBuild` hook\n- Generates `search-index.json` in ctx.output\n- Index is JSON array of objects with: `slug`, `title`, `content` (plain text), `tags` (optional)\n- HTML tags must be stripped from content\n- Code blocks included in searchable text\n- Handles empty file list → `[]`\n- Valid JSON output\n\n**Tests:**\n1. Generates search-index.json in ctx.output\n2. Index entries have title, slug, and plain text content\n3. HTML tags stripped from indexed content\n4. Code blocks included in searchable text\n5. Handles empty file list\n6. Search index is valid JSON\n7. Index entries include tags if present\n\n---\n\n#### **B. rss-feed.test.ts**\n\nCreates RSS 2.0 feed in afterBuild hook.\n\n**Requirements:**\n- Plugin name: likely \"rss-feed\"\n- Has `afterBuild` hook\n- Generates `feed.xml` in ctx.output\n- Valid RSS 2.0 structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`, `</rss>`\n- Feed items contain HTML content (wrapped in CDATA)\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Channel title from config.title\n- Links use config.baseUrl\n- Includes category tags from taxonomy data (`ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')`)\n- Handles files without dates gracefully\n\n**Tests:**\n1. Generates valid RSS 2.0 XML\n2. Feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown (CDATA wrapped)\n3. Feed items include category tags from taxonomy\n4. Feed includes channel title from config\n5. Feed items sorted by date newest first\n6. Handles files without dates\n7. Feed link uses baseUrl from config\n\n---\n\n#### **C. sitemap.test.ts**\n\nCreates XML sitemap in afterBuild hook.\n\n**Requirements:**\n- Plugin name: likely \"sitemap\"\n- Has `afterBuild` hook\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` in ctx.output\n- Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>`, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`\n- Includes all HTML files from ctx.output\n- Includes feed.xml if present\n- Includes tag pages from taxonomy data (`ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')`)\n- URLs constructed as `{config.baseUrl}/{file-path}`\n\n**Tests:**\n1. Generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output\n2. Includes all content page URLs\n3. Includes taxonomy tag page URLs\n4. Includes feed.xml URL\n5. URLs use baseUrl from config\n6. Sitemap is valid XML structure\n7. Handles site with no tag pages\n\n---\n\n#### **D. dev-server.test.ts**\n\nStores dev server configuration in ctx.data in afterBuild hook.\n\n**Requirements:**\n- Plugin name: likely \"dev-server\"\n- Has `afterBuild` hook\n- Stores `dev-server-config` in ctx.data\n- Config type has:\n  - `port: number` (default: 3000)\n  - `routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>`\n  - `assetPaths: string[]`\n  - `searchIndexPath: string`\n- Routes include:\n  - Static content routes for each HTML file in ctx.output (handler: \"static\")\n  - Asset routes from asset-pipeline data (handler: \"asset\")\n- Reads asset-pipeline data: `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` → `{ assets: string[] }`\n- Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\n**Tests:**\n1. Stores dev-server-config in ctx.data\n2. Config includes port setting\n3. Config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline\n4. Config includes search index path\n5. Config includes content routes\n6. Default port is 3000\n7. Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\n---\n\n#### **E. asset-pipeline.test.ts**\n\nRewrites asset URLs and tracks assets in transformContent hook.\n\n**Requirements:**\n- Plugin name: likely \"asset-pipeline\"\n- Has `transformContent` hook\n- Rewrites relative URLs to `/assets/` path:\n  - `<img src=\"./image.png\">` → `<img src=\"/assets/image.png\">`\n  - `<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">` → `<a href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\">`\n  - Matches src and href attributes\n  - Does NOT rewrite absolute URLs (starting with http/https)\n  - Does NOT rewrite already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs\n- Generates `asset-manifest` in ctx.data: `{ assets: string[] }`\n- Accumulates all discovered assets across multiple files\n- Extracts filenames from asset URLs\n\n**Tests:**\n1. Rewrites relative image URLs to /assets/ path\n2. Rewrites relative link URLs to /assets/ path\n3. Leaves absolute URLs unchanged\n4. Generates asset manifest in ctx.data\n5. Handles files with no asset references\n6. Handles multiple assets in one file\n7. Asset manifest includes all discovered assets\n8. Does not double-process already-rewritten URLs\n\n---\n\n#### **F. taxonomy.test.ts**\n\nBuilds tag index and generates tag listing pages.\n\n**Requirements:**\n- Plugin name: likely \"taxonomy\"\n- Has `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild` hooks\n- **beforeBuild:*